{
  "stem": "812.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "We were excited.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "We were naive, and we were excited that there was going to be a change in our lives and hoping, of course, for the better.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And the adults and parents somehow realized that things were going to get a lot worse for us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] it was in February of 1944 that it was our turn to be shipped out of Westerbork.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "We were allowed to take [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] just a knapsack a person, and whatever we could fit into the knapsack that-- those were our belongings, and that was it.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "We [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] had the privilege of being sent to Bergen-Belsen as opposed to Auschwitz, because arrangements were made through my mother's sister, who lived in Palestine at the time, for us to be exchanged for a group of German religious sect-- I think it was called the Templars-- who were in Palestine, and we were to be exchanged for them.",
      "word_count": 63
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "She made arrangements, and we would be among the few hundred of those.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "Initially, there were 1,000 or so, but then it was cut back to a few hundred, and we were to be among that group to be exchanged.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And therefore, we were a privileged-- within that privileged group to be sent to Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] As I said, in February we were walked to the station of Westerbork.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And as we saw the trains, cattle cars, our fears began to mount.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And we realized that our hopes, my hopes as a child-- at that time I was nine years old-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] that things were not going to be as easy or as comfortable as we had hoped it would be.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "We [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] got on the train.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
